{{Infobox football club | clubname = Publique Sportive Mouara| image = | fullname = Publique Sportive Mouara| nickname = | founded = | ground = [[Barthelemy Boganda Stadium]]| capacity = 35000| chairman = {{flagicon|CAF}}?| manager = {{flagicon|CAF}}?| league = [[Central African Republic League]]| season = | position = | }}
'''Publique Sportive Mouara''' is an [[association football]] club from [[Central African Republic]] based in [[Bangui]].
The team has won the [[Central African Republic League]] in 1981 and 1986.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesc/cafrchamp.html|title=Central African Republic - List of Champions|last=Bobrowsky|first=Josef|last2=Schöggl|first2=Hans|date=7 December 2017|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>
==Stadium== Currently the team plays at the 35,000 capacity [[Barthelemy Boganda Stadium]].
==Honours== *[[Central African Republic League]]: 1981, 1986
