{{Infobox venue | name = T. Henry Wilson Jr. Field | nickname = Wilson Field | image = | fullname = | former_names = Wildcat Park | location = 202 Martin Court Drive, [[Davidson, North Carolina|Davidson]], [[North Carolina|NC]], [[United States of America|USA]] | coordinates = {{coord|35.503753|-80.841208|display=title,inline}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = March 19, 1967 | renovated = 2003, 2005, 2009 | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Davidson College]] | operator = | surface = Natural [[grass]] | scoreboard = Electronic | estimated_cost = | suites = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 700 | record_attendance = | executive_suites = | dimensions = 320 ft. ([[Left field|LF]]), 385 ([[Baseball field#outfield|CF]]), 325 ft. ([[Right field|RF]]) | acreage = | tenants = [[Davidson Wildcats]] [[College baseball|baseball]] (2001-present) }}
'''T. Henry Wilson Jr. Field''' is a [[baseball]] [[Baseball field|venue]] located in [[Davidson, North Carolina|Davidson]], [[North Carolina]], United States. It is home to the [[Davidson Wildcats]] [[College baseball|baseball]] team, a member of the [[Division I (NCAA)|Division I]] [[Atlantic-10 Conference]].<ref name="facil">[http://www.davidsonwildcats.com/sports/2007/8/24/FacilWilson.aspx Wilson Field] at davidsonwildcats.com, URL accessed June 30, 2010. [https://www.webcitation.org/5qsryk2iw Archived] 06-30-10</ref> It has a capacity of 700 spectators.<ref name="qf">[http://www.davidsonwildcats.com/sports/2010/1/7/BB_0107104519.aspx?path=baseball 2010 Baseball Quick Facts] at davidsonwildcats.com, URL accessed June 30, 2010. [https://www.webcitation.org/5qss54Vmb Archived] 06-30-10</ref>
The field opened in 1967 as '''Wildcat Park''', with the first game being held on March 19, 1967. On March 19, 2005, the venue was renamed after T. Henry Wilson Jr., class of 1951. Wilson played both [[college baseball|baseball]] and [[college football|football]] at Davidson, and a donation by his family made significant renovations to the field possible.<ref name="facil" />
In 2003, lights were installed at the facility, allowing the first night games to be played at then-Wildcat Park. In 2005, after a donation from the Wilson family, new [[bleachers]], [[infield]], [[concession stand]]s, and a [[press box]] were added. In 2009, an indoor practice facility outside the field was completed.<ref name="facil" />
